{"questionId":"9075188","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Sirius is a binary star. It is composed of two stars, Sirius A and Sirius B. Sirius A is a&nbsp;main sequence star.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The Sun’s surface temperature is about 5800 K.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Determine the radius of Sirius B in terms of the radius of the Sun.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\left( {\\frac{{{L_{\\,{\\text{Sirius}}\\,{\\text{B}}}}}}{{L{\\,_{{\\text{Sun}}}}}}} \\right)\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mfrac>\n        <mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <msub>\n              <mi>L</mi>\n              <mrow>\n                <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n                <mrow>\n                  <mtext>Sirius</mtext>\n                </mrow>\n                <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n                <mrow>\n                  <mtext>B</mtext>\n                </mrow>\n              </mrow>\n            </msub>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n        <mrow>\n          <mi>L</mi>\n          <mrow>\n            <msub>\n              <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n              <mrow>\n                <mrow>\n                  <mtext>Sun</mtext>\n                </mrow>\n              </mrow>\n            </msub>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n      </mfrac>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> = 0.025</p>\n<p><em>r </em><sub>Sirius</sub> =&nbsp;«<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\sqrt {0.025 \\times {{\\left( {\\frac{{5800}}{{25000}}} \\right)}^4}} \">\n  <msqrt>\n    <mn>0.025</mn>\n    <mo>×</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <msup>\n        <mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <mo>(</mo>\n            <mrow>\n              <mfrac>\n                <mrow>\n                  <mn>5800</mn>\n                </mrow>\n  